Hello,
I have a Doublestar AR-15 upper in 6.5 Grendel. It has a 20" threaded barrel. I've had good luck with it, and I'm able to average .8-.9 MOA 5 shot groups with it. It pushes a 123gr bullet at about 2430 fps. The upper has an Odinworks free-float rail that comes with a 3" picatinny attachment that you can move wherever. I've also threaded in a standard sling swivel for a harris-style bipod.
I'm selling everything you need to convert your .223 AR to 6.5 Grendel, so this kit will come with the upper, a bolt, and two magazines. I also have a set of nice Hornady reloading dies with a case holder that I'll toss in for an extra $25.
6.5 Grendel is a pretty cool caliber, and it actually out performs a .308 AR-10 in windage and energy at long ranges. It fits in a lighter weight AR-15 platform, and the recoil is pretty mild. I'd say it's only about 10% more than when I'm using my .223 upper.
$550 for the Grendel kit, and $575 for the kit plus the reloading dies. The only trade I'm open to would be for a precision .223 bolt action rifle with a 1:9 or faster twist.
